<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Uninstall 3rd Party App]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7204&amp;p=30924#p30924"><![CDATA[
No, right click on Start button -&gt; Settings will open Classic Shell Settings which are different from Windows Settings.<br /><br />To uninstall an app in Windows 10, press Win+i keys together on your keyboard to open the Windows Settings app. From there, the rest of the instructions you posted are correct. Go to System - Apps &amp; features. Select the app and click Uninstall.<br /><br />Another way to uninstall an app when Classic Shell is installed is to go to Start -&gt; All Programs -&gt; Apps folder. Locate your app and right click it -&gt; Uninstall.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Mon Dec 26, 2016 8:46 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
