<span style="font-size: 100%; line-height: 116%;">I am running Classic Shell on Win 10 Home. I downloaded a free app from the MS App store which I now want to uninstall. I go to my control panel Programs and Features and it is not listed. To uninstall an app in Win 10 I think I am supposed right click on the Start Button, choose Settings and <span style="color:#222222;"><span style="font-family:Roboto, arial, sans-serif;">Select System and then tap</span></span><strong><span style="color:#222222;"><span style="font-family:Roboto, arial, sans-serif;">Apps</span></span></strong><span style="color:#222222;"><span style="font-family:Roboto, arial, sans-serif;">&amp; features. You can sort the list of</span></span><strong><span style="color:#222222;"><span style="font-family:Roboto, arial, sans-serif;">apps</span></span></strong><span style="color:#222222;"><span style="font-family:Roboto, arial, sans-serif;">by size, name, or install date. If you would like to</span></span><strong><span style="color:#222222;"><span style="font-family:Roboto, arial, sans-serif;">uninstall</span></span></strong><span style="color:#222222;"><span style="font-family:Roboto, arial, sans-serif;">an</span></span><strong><span style="color:#222222;"><span style="font-family:Roboto, arial, sans-serif;">app</span></span></strong><span style="color:#222222;"><span style="font-family:Roboto, arial, sans-serif;">, select it from the list and then tap or click the</span></span><strong><span style="color:#222222;"><span style="font-family:Roboto, arial, sans-serif;">uninstall.</span></span></strong><br /><strong><span style="color:#222222;"><span style="font-family:Roboto, arial, sans-serif;">I only see the Classic Shell settings when I do this, not the Windows system settings. Ideas?</span></span></strong></span><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=16870">24Peter</a> — Mon Dec 26, 2016 4:28 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
